						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The surname Brewster originally meant &quot;woman who makes beer&quot;.<br /><br />But in the 14th century, men wanted in on the alcohol market. So they got all sexist, reinterpreting the signs of a brewer as signs of witchcraft.</div><br /><br />Coincidentally, &quot;witch&quot; in Spanish is the similar-sounding &quot;bruja&quot;. The actual etymology of it is pretty unclear, though, and it doesn't resemble the equivalent word in any other Romance languages that I'm familiar with.</div>

